<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="435" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1477,2044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1514,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is derived from the Latin “vappo”, meaning a variety of nocturnal moth. It refers both to the spiders being collected from the dark zone of a cave and to the copulatory ducts in the females which are shaped like the wings of a moth. The second part of the name “-loetes” comes from 
<taxonomicName authority="Blackwall, 1841" authorityName="Blackwall" authorityYear="1841" box="[1140,1431,1586,1612]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Coelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1140,1238,1586,1612]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Coelotes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blackwall, J." box="[1245,1431,1586,1612]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" pagination="601 - 670" refId="ref3519" refString="Blackwall, J. (1841) The difference in the number of eyes with which spiders are provided proposed as the basis of their distribu- tion into tribes; with descriptions of newly discovered species and the characters of a new family and three new genera of spiders. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, 18, 601 - 670. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1838. tb 00210. x" type="journal article" year="1841">Blackwall, 1841</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, referring to the similarity with the nominal genus of the subfamily. The gender is masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="435" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1477,2044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1657,1684]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[380,428,1658,1684]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">type</typeStatus>
species of the new genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang" authorityYear="2002" box="[868,1025,1658,1684]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Longicoelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[868,1025,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Longicoelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[1040,1381,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang" authorityYear="2002" box="[1040,1195,1658,1684]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Platocoelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Platocoelotes</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhao et Li" authorityYear="2016" box="[1207,1381,1658,1684]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Papiliocoelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Papiliocoelotes</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,297,1694,1720]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Spiricoelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,297,1694,1720]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Spiricoelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the slender embolus (
<figureCitation box="[580,703,1694,1720]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left male palp of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Prolateral view; B, Ventral view; C, Retrolateral view. Scale bar: equal for A, B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
), the small or absent median apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1249,1694,1720]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left male palp of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Prolateral view; B, Ventral view; C, Retrolateral view. Scale bar: equal for A, B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
), and the lack of epigynal teeth (
<figureCitation box="[327,421,1730,1756]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[435,473,1730,1756]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes jianpingensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Female habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, ventral; E, Female habitus, lateral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559393/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">4A</figureCitation>
). The new genus is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhao et Li" authorityYear="2016" box="[881,1055,1730,1756]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Papiliocoelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[881,1055,1730,1756]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Papiliocoelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with which it shares a bifurcated tegular apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[361,479,1766,1792]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left male palp of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Prolateral view; B, Ventral view; C, Retrolateral view. Scale bar: equal for A, B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Fig. 2B, C</figureCitation>
). However, the male of the new genus can be easily distinguished from males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhao et Li" authorityYear="2016" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Papiliocoelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Papiliocoelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a dorsal apophysis and a lamella of the conductor (
<figureCitation box="[953,1019,1802,1828]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left male palp of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Prolateral view; B, Ventral view; C, Retrolateral view. Scale bar: equal for A, B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A–C), whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhao et Li" authorityYear="2016" box="[1221,1395,1802,1828]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Papiliocoelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1221,1395,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Papiliocoelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the conductor has a slightly bifurcated distal process and lacks a lamella (fig.1A–C in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhao, Z. &amp; Li, S." box="[1064,1273,1837,1864]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" pagination="33 - 50" refId="ref4708" refString="Zhao, Z. &amp; Li, S. (2016) Papiliocoelotes gen. n., a new genus of Coelotinae (Araneae, Agelenidae) spiders from the Wuling Mountains, China. ZooKeys, 585, 33 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 585.8007" type="journal article" year="2016">Zhao and Li, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally, in 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Zhao &amp; Chen &amp; Chen &amp; Wu &amp; Li, 2019" authorityName="Li &amp; Zhao &amp; Chen &amp; Chen &amp; Wu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2019" box="[179,302,1874,1900]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Vappolotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[179,302,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Vappolotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the tegular apophysis is bifurcated at the base (
<figureCitation box="[832,950,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left male palp of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Prolateral view; B, Ventral view; C, Retrolateral view. Scale bar: equal for A, B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Fig. 2B, C</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhao et Li" authorityYear="2016" box="[1096,1270,1874,1900]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Papiliocoelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1096,1270,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Papiliocoelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is bifurcated at the tip (fig. 2A, B in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhao, Z. &amp; Li, S." box="[406,614,1909,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" pagination="33 - 50" refId="ref4708" refString="Zhao, Z. &amp; Li, S. (2016) Papiliocoelotes gen. n., a new genus of Coelotinae (Araneae, Agelenidae) spiders from the Wuling Mountains, China. ZooKeys, 585, 33 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 585.8007" type="journal article" year="2016">Zhao and Li, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The female of the new genus can be easily distinguished from females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhao et Li" authorityYear="2016" box="[151,325,1946,1972]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Papiliocoelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,325,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Papiliocoelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the bracketed lateral edges of the epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[872,966,1946,1972]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[978,1016,1946,1972]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes jianpingensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Female habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, ventral; E, Female habitus, lateral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559393/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">4A</figureCitation>
); in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhao et Li" authorityYear="2016" box="[1065,1239,1946,1972]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Papiliocoelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1065,1239,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Papiliocoelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the lateral edges are concave medially (fig. 2A in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhao, Z. &amp; Li, S." box="[512,721,1981,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" pagination="33 - 50" refId="ref4708" refString="Zhao, Z. &amp; Li, S. (2016) Papiliocoelotes gen. n., a new genus of Coelotinae (Araneae, Agelenidae) spiders from the Wuling Mountains, China. ZooKeys, 585, 33 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 585.8007" type="journal article" year="2016">Zhao and Li, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).Also, in 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Zhao &amp; Chen &amp; Chen &amp; Wu &amp; Li, 2019" authorityName="Li &amp; Zhao &amp; Chen &amp; Chen &amp; Wu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2019" box="[830,953,1982,2008]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Vappolotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[830,953,1982,2008]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Vappolotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the epigynal hoods are located anterolaterally (
<figureCitation box="[209,297,2018,2044]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[309,347,2018,2044]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes jianpingensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Female habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, ventral; E, Female habitus, lateral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559393/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">4A</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhao et Li" authorityYear="2016" box="[494,668,2018,2044]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Papiliocoelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[494,668,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Papiliocoelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are located mediolaterally (fig. 2A in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhao, Z. &amp; Li, S." box="[1151,1363,2017,2044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" pagination="33 - 50" refId="ref4708" refString="Zhao, Z. &amp; Li, S. (2016) Papiliocoelotes gen. n., a new genus of Coelotinae (Araneae, Agelenidae) spiders from the Wuling Mountains, China. ZooKeys, 585, 33 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 585.8007" type="journal article" year="2016">Zhao and Li, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="436" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,664]" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,152,179]" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Description.</emphasis>
Medium sized, with a total length of 
<quantity box="[784,882,152,179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="436" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
. Body color yellow-brown generally, with black stripes (
<figureCitation box="[240,305,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C–E); chelicerae with 3 promarginal and 2 retromarginal teeth in both sexes; carapace yellow-brown with radial pattern, pear-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[521,643,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 3C, D</figureCitation>
); clypeus yellow-brown or brown (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1125,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); endites and labium brown (
<figureCitation box="[160,246,257,283]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); sternum yellow-brown (
<figureCitation box="[532,618,257,283]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); legs yellow-brown with the formula 4&gt; 1&gt; 2&gt; 3 (
<figureCitation box="[1196,1260,257,283]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C–E); abdomen gray or yellow-brown, oval, with 3–4 chevrons posterodorsally (
<figureCitation box="[870,991,291,318]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 3C, D</figureCitation>
); spinnerets yellow-brown (
<figureCitation box="[1304,1369,291,318]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C–E). Male palp with one patellar apophysis, one retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA), and a ventrolateral tibial apophysis (VTA) (
<figureCitation box="[240,329,361,387]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left male palp of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Prolateral view; B, Ventral view; C, Retrolateral view. Scale bar: equal for A, B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559389/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
); median apophysis absent; cymbial furrow less than 1/2 the length of cymbium (
<figureCitation box="[1237,1326,361,387]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left male palp of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Prolateral view; B, Ventral view; C, Retrolateral view. Scale bar: equal for A, B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559389/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
); conduc- tor with a lamella (LC) and a dorsal apophysis (CDA) (
<figureCitation box="[765,879,395,422]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left male palp of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Prolateral view; B, Ventral view; C, Retrolateral view. Scale bar: equal for A, B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559389/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig.2A, B</figureCitation>
); tegulum brown, sclerite of tegulum (ST) as long as embolic base (EB), and tegular apophysis bifurcated (
<figureCitation box="[800,868,430,456]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left male palp of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Prolateral view; B, Ventral view; C, Retrolateral view. Scale bar: equal for A, B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559389/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A–C); subtegulum with many wrinkles (
<figureCitation box="[1330,1423,430,456]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left male palp of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Prolateral view; B, Ventral view; C, Retrolateral view. Scale bar: equal for A, B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559389/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); embolus filiform and long (
<figureCitation box="[464,587,465,491]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,941,1829]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left male palp of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Prolateral view; B, Ventral view; C, Retrolateral view. Scale bar: equal for A, B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559389/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
). Epigynum with deep anterolateral hoods (
<figureCitation box="[1083,1177,465,491]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1190,1228,465,491]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes jianpingensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Female habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, ventral; E, Female habitus, lateral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">4A</figureCitation>
); atrium relatively large, with lateral and posterolateral margins conspicuous (
<figureCitation box="[808,900,499,526]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[912,950,500,526]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes jianpingensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Female habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, ventral; E, Female habitus, lateral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">4A</figureCitation>
); epigynal teeth and median septum absent; copulatory openings located posteromedially (
<figureCitation box="[668,761,534,560]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[773,811,534,560]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes jianpingensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Female habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, ventral; E, Female habitus, lateral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">4A</figureCitation>
); copulatory ducts broad and transparent, like the wings of a moth (
<figureCitation box="[272,363,569,595]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Figs 3B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[375,411,569,595]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes jianpingensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Female habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, ventral; E, Female habitus, lateral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">4B</figureCitation>
); spermathecae nephroid, spermathecal bases close to each other (
<figureCitation box="[1147,1238,569,595]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Figs 3B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1249,1285,569,595]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes jianpingensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Female habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, ventral; E, Female habitus, lateral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">4B</figureCitation>
); fertilization ducts at least twice as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[557,649,603,630]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes ganlongensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Male habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, dorsal; E, Female habitus, ventral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Figs 3B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[661,697,604,630]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1333,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Epigynum and habitus of Vappolotes jianpingensis sp. n. A, Epigynum, ventral; B, Internal genitalia, dorsal; C, Female habitus, dorsal; D, Female habitus, ventral; E, Female habitus, lateral. Scale bars: equal for A and B, equal for C, D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3559393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">4B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
